286
00:15:45,996 --> 00:15:47,898
They didn't want to have
a child,

287
00:15:47,898 --> 00:15:49,799
And my mom took something,
some tablets.

288
00:15:49,799 --> 00:15:54,237
He got some tablets off another
drummer to get rid of me.

289
00:15:54,237 --> 00:15:56,006
I don't care.
[Laughs]

290
00:15:56,006 --> 00:15:58,508
They would have been doing me
a bloody favor.

291
00:15:58,508 --> 00:16:00,743
No, I don't mind,
but it didn't work.

292
00:16:00,743 --> 00:16:01,945
[Laughs]

293
00:16:01,945 --> 00:16:03,513
No screaming or anything.

294
00:16:03,513 --> 00:16:04,614
The baby come out.

295
00:16:04,614 --> 00:16:06,249
And I'm carefully looking

296
00:16:06,249 --> 00:16:09,019
To make sure it's got all
its toes and fingers and stuff,

297
00:16:09,019 --> 00:16:11,021
You know,
thinking about the time

298
00:16:11,021 --> 00:16:15,158
We tried to abort it and stuff.

299
00:16:15,158 --> 00:16:17,460
There was this little kid.

300
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:21,097
And that's when I decided
to get straight,

301
00:16:21,097 --> 00:16:25,701
And it took me
another fucking 19 years or so.

302
00:16:25,701 --> 00:16:27,303
So, what's the difference

303
00:16:27,303 --> 00:16:30,206
Between your state
of chemical dependencies now

304
00:16:30,206 --> 00:16:32,375
Than it was
when you were a junkie?

305
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:34,810
