00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:23,873
Don't worry about
splitting your skins.

383
00:20:23,873 --> 00:20:26,809
They can be replaced.

384
00:20:26,809 --> 00:20:28,744
And so can you.

385
00:20:28,744 --> 00:20:32,648
They did sort of contain the
seeds of their own destruction,

386
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:35,418
What with Graham
and Ginger's bad habits

387
00:20:35,418 --> 00:20:38,221
And the conflict
between Jack and Ginger.

388
00:20:38,221 --> 00:20:39,689
For two musicians

389
00:20:39,689 --> 00:20:42,492
Who were incredibly
complementary to each other

390
00:20:42,492 --> 00:20:45,027
And who have played
consistently over the years,

391
00:20:45,027 --> 00:20:50,733
It's really remarkable
how well they didn't get along.

392
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:54,036
It was a very sad
situation, really.

393
00:20:54,036 --> 00:20:58,208
In the early days,
when he was following me more,

394
00:20:58,208 --> 00:21:00,710
The music was
really fucking great.

395
00:21:00,710 --> 00:21:04,580
When I switched from
upright bass to bass guitar,

396
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:06,849
That wasn't what Ginger wanted.

397
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:10,085
I think that was when
