414
00:22:01,504 --> 00:22:04,340
You know,
"Get up, you little cunt!"

415
00:22:04,340 --> 00:22:06,809
I was kicking the shit
out of him.

416
00:22:06,809 --> 00:22:08,678
[Drum solo]

417
00:22:08,678 --> 00:22:13,816
I just let go, and I was gonna
kick him to death.

418
00:22:13,816 --> 00:22:17,219
And then he pulled a knife
on me and said, "You're fired."

419
00:22:17,219 --> 00:22:18,788
And I said,
"But you can't fire me.

420
00:22:18,788 --> 00:22:21,090
"It's The Graham Bond
Organization,

421
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:22,592
And I'm the founding member."

422
00:22:22,592 --> 00:22:23,893
But poor old Graham...

423
00:22:23,893 --> 00:22:26,262
He was well gone
into smack by that time,

424
00:22:26,262 --> 00:22:27,930
So he didn't really care.

425
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:32,067
Graham was probably a bigger
disaster area than Ginger was.

426
00:22:32,067 --> 00:22:35,271
We would be using a mixture
of cocaine, heroin,

427
00:22:35,271 --> 00:22:37,840
And lysergic acid in a fix.

428
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:39,008
[Laughs]

429
00:22:39,008 --> 00:22:43,346
I was very hurt
by not the knife thing,

430
00:22:43,346 --> 00:22:47,182
But the fact that I was out
of that band.

431
00:22:47,182 --> 00:22:51,721
And it was very stupid of him,
because the band was doing well,

432
00:22:51,721 --> 00:22:55,024
And I was quite an important
part of the band.

433
00:22:55,024 --> 00:22:58,794
The band continued
being very successful

434
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:01,931
And just reached a point
where I thought,

435
00:23:01,931 --> 00:23:06,536
"I've been running the band
successfully for three years.

436
00:23:06,536 --> 00:23:10,573
Why don't I run my own band
instead?"

437
00:23:10,573 --> 00:23:14,377
[Cream's "White Room" plays]

438
00:23:22,385 --> 00:23:27,156
The first person I thought of
was Eric.

439
00:23:27,156 --> 00:23:30,760
[Guitar solo]

440
00:23:34,997 --> 00:23:38,434
He saw something in me
that I never saw before.

441
00:23:38,434 --> 00:23:40,436
He would say it was about time.

442
00:23:40,436 --> 00:23:43,873
He had time
that very few people have.

443
00:23:43,873 --> 00:23:45,074
Eric had it.

444
00:23:45,074 --> 00:23:48,678
Ginger was pretty dismissive
and antisocial...

445
00:23:48,678 --> 00:23:50,413
Seriously antisocial.

446
00:23:50,413 --> 00:23:52,415
But he had the gift.

447
00:23:52,415 --> 00:23:55,685
He had the spark, the flair,
the panache.

448
00:23:55,685 --> 00:23:57,387
He had it in spades.

449
00:23:57,387 --> 00:23:59,489
And Jack had the same thing.

450
00:23:59,489 --> 00:24:02,958
He said, "What about Jack
as the bass player?"

451
00:24:02,958 --> 00:24:06,228
And all the red lights
in the world went off,

452
00:24:06,228 --> 00:24:08,263
And I thought, "Oh, God."

453
00:24:08,263 --> 00:24:11,934
I was very surprised
when he came knocking again.

454
00:24:11,934 --> 00:24:13,969
