00:24:46,201 --> 00:24:48,971
When an atomic bomb
went off like that,

465
00:24:48,971 --> 00:24:51,373
Like I think Cream
really represented,

466
00:24:51,373 --> 00:24:53,476
It overwhelmed everything.

467
00:24:53,476 --> 00:24:57,447
["Tales of Brave Ulysses"
plays]

468
00:25:01,951 --> 00:25:06,221
When Hendrix came to England,
he wanted to jam with Cream,

469
00:25:06,221 --> 00:25:09,091
Because there was nobody else
that he admired as much.

470
00:25:09,091 --> 00:25:12,361
They were the beginning
of many, many things.

471
00:25:12,361 --> 00:25:13,663
Cream absolutely
might be called

472
00:25:13,663 --> 00:25:15,130
The first progressive band.

473
00:25:15,130 --> 00:25:16,499
The first supergroup.

474
00:25:16,499 --> 00:25:18,734
The first band that played
in big arenas.

475
00:25:18,734 --> 00:25:20,202
The first jam band.

476
00:25:20,202 --> 00:25:23,739
They were breaking out
of the chains of pop.

477
00:25:30,446 --> 00:25:32,047
We were fucking good.

478
00:25:32,047 --> 00:25:35,084
That's how we called ourselves
Cream.

479
00:25:35,084 --> 00:25:38,854
We knew we were the three
best musicians around.

480
00:25:38,854 --> 00:25:40,990
If Cream did not invent
heavy metal,

481
00:25:40,990 --> 00:25:43,926
They certainly were part
of a band of brothers

482
00:25:43,926 --> 00:25:46,929
That were very instrumental
in facilitating it.

483
00:25:46,929 --> 00:25:52,134
The birth of heavy metal
should have been aborted.

484
00:25:52,735 --> 00:25:54,937
He was really at the forefront

485
00:25:54,937 --> 00:25:57,540
Of a complete revolution
of rock.

486
00:25:57,540 --> 00:26:00,743
["Sunshine of Your Love"
plays]

487
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:06,916
It's hard to find fault
with the notion

488
00:26:06,916 --> 00:26:08,951
That he was the pioneer
of a rock drummer.

489
00:26:08,951 --> 00:26:12,221
There was no context for him.
There was no archetype.

490
00:26:12,221 --> 00:26:13,623
He is the archetype.

491
00:26:13,623 --> 00:26:15,491
Before Ginger, rhythm was

492
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:17,292
"Ting, ting, ting-ting,
ting, ting-ting."

493
00:26:17,292 --> 00:26:18,828
And Ginger comes along...

494
00:26:18,828 --> 00:26:21,764
"Dug-a-dug-dug, dug-a-dug-dug,
Dug-dug-dug-a-dug..."

